How can I use Python to analyze the relationship between mental health and creativity? Here is a sample code that can be modified:
object MentalHealthCreativity {
  def main(args: Array[String]): Unit = {
    val creativity_scores = List(7, 9, 5, 8, 6, 10, 4, 7, 8, 6)
    val mental_health_scores = List(15, 12, 16, 9, 11, 18, 14, 17, 13, 10)
    val correlation = calculate_correlation(creativity_scores, mental_health_scores)
    if (correlation > 0.5) {
      println("There may be a strong positive relationship between mental health and creativity.")
    } else {
      println("There may not be a significant relationship between mental health and creativity.")
    }
  }

  def calculate_correlation(xs: List[Double], ys: List[Double]): Double = {
    val x_avg = xs.sum / xs.length
    val y_avg = ys.sum / ys.length
    val numerator = xs.zip(ys).map(xy => (xy._1 - x_avg) * (xy._2 - y_avg)).sum
    val xs_diff = xs.map(x => math.pow(x - x_avg, 2)).sum
    val ys_diff = ys.map(y => math.pow(y - y_avg, 2)).sum
    val denominator = math.sqrt(xs_diff * ys_diff)
    numerator / denominator
  }
}
This code calculates the correlation between creativity scores and mental health scores. If the correlation is strong, it suggests that mental health may have an impact on creativity. You can modify the code to analyze different factors that may influence mental health and creativity.
